Kebbi Governor Atiku Bagudu on Tuesday condoled the family of a renowned Islamic cleric, Malam Abubakar Nassarawa, who died following injuries sustained in a road accident along Zaria- Funtua-Gusau road on Thursday, May 2. In a statement signed by Bagudu’s Chief Press Secretary, Abubakar Dakingarim in Birnin Kebbi, Bagudu prayed to God to grant the decease Aljannah Firdausi. Nasarawa died at the age of 78, leaving behind three wives and 35 children and several grandchildren. NAN